INTRODUCTION
This project was completed as part of the Digital Literacy course, where I was assigned the role of a Student Digital Ambassador. The objective of this project was to understand and apply essential digital skills required in today’s academic and professional environment. Through a series of five tasks, I explored various aspects of digital literacy, including creating awareness through visual content, building a professional online presence, using coding and collaboration platforms, practicing professional communication, and understanding cybercrime risks. Each task helped me gain practical experience and improved my confidence in using digital tools effectively. This project also emphasized the importance of responsible and safe online behavior. Overall, it provided valuable insights into how digital literacy plays a crucial role in personal and professional growth.
________________________________________
TASK 1: DIGITAL LITERACY INFOGRAPHIC
For Task 1, I created a digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva. The purpose of this infographic was to educate students about the importance of digital literacy in a simple and visually engaging manner. The design included key topics such as the definition of digital literacy, useful digital tools for students, safe internet practices, professional online presence, and email etiquette. I selected Canva as my design tool because it offers a wide range of templates, icons, and customization options, making it easy to create professional-looking designs without prior experience. While designing the infographic, I focused on keeping the content concise and easy to understand so that it could effectively communicate the message to my peers. One challenge I faced was balancing visual appeal with content clarity, as adding too much information could make the design cluttered. This task helped me improve my ability to present information creatively and reinforced the importance of spreading digital awareness.
________________________________________
TASK 2: DIGITAL PORTFOLIO
In Task 2, I developed my digital portfolio by creating profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle. These platforms are essential for building a professional online presence. GitHub is widely used for showcasing coding projects and tracking development progress, which will help me build a strong technical portfolio over time. LinkedIn serves as a professional networking platform where I can connect with peers, professors, and industry professionals, as well as explore internship and job opportunities. Kaggle is a platform for data science and machine learning, where I can practice problem-solving and participate in competitions. Setting up these profiles helped me understand how important it is to maintain a professional identity online. Over the next four years, I plan to actively use these platforms to upload projects, improve my technical skills, and expand my professional network. This task gave me a strong foundation for my future career development.
________________________________________
TASK 3: CODING AND COLLABORATION PLATFORMS
For Task 3, I explored coding and collaboration platforms. I used HackerRank to solve a beginner-level programming problem, which helped me understand basic coding concepts such as input, output, and problem-solving logic. This experience was useful in building my confidence as a beginner in programming. Additionally, I created a Google Form titled “Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz” consisting of five questions to test students’ knowledge of digital literacy. The form included both multiple-choice and short-answer questions. I also linked the responses to a Google Sheet, which allows easy data collection and analysis. This task demonstrated how digital tools can be used effectively for both learning and collaboration. Coding platforms help improve logical thinking and technical skills, while tools like Google Forms enable efficient communication and data management. Overall, this task enhanced my understanding of how technology can support academic activities.
________________________________________
TASK 4: EMAIL ETIQUETTE AND DIGITAL COMMUNICATION
In Task 4, I learned about professional communication through email writing and social media etiquette. I drafted two emails: one requesting an assignment extension from a professor and another expressing interest in a summer internship. This helped me understand the importance of maintaining a polite tone, clear subject line, and proper structure in professional emails. I also created a checklist of do’s and don’ts for responsible social media usage. Poor digital communication can lead to misunderstandings and negative impressions. For example, sending an unclear or informal email to a professor may result in confusion or lack of response. This could be avoided by following proper email etiquette. This task improved my communication skills and made me more aware of how to present myself professionally online.
________________________________________
TASK 5: CYBERCRIME AWARENESS
In Task 5, I explored cybercrime awareness by studying UPI fraud. I learned that many people fall victim to scams due to lack of awareness, especially when they unknowingly approve payment requests or share sensitive information like OTPs. What surprised me the most was how easily scammers can manipulate users into making mistakes. This task helped me understand the importance of being cautious while using digital payment platforms. I also created a prevention checklist with practical safety measures such as not sharing OTPs, avoiding suspicious links, and verifying transactions carefully. As a result of this task, I will be more careful while making online transactions and will always follow safe practices. This task increased my awareness of online threats and the importance of digital security.
________________________________________
CONCLUSION
Overall, this project helped me develop a strong understanding of digital literacy and its importance in modern life. Each task provided practical experience in different areas, including design, professional networking, coding, communication, and cybersecurity. I learned how to use digital tools effectively and responsibly, as well as how to present myself professionally online. This project also made me more aware of online risks and how to stay safe while using digital platforms. The skills I gained from this project will be useful throughout my academic journey and future career. It was a valuable learning experience that enhanced both my technical and communication skills.
